AM Radio

KFXN

Frequency: 690 AM

Genre: Hmong American news, talk and entertainment

This Asian station plays classic and today’s top Hmong American music. It also broadcasts local, national and international news in Hmong/Lao and other Asian languages.

WDGY – WDGY The Original Rock ‘n’ Roll Station

Frequency: 740 AM

Genre: Oldies

“Wee Gee” plays legendary rock ‘n’ roll artists from the 1960s and ’70s. Paul Geiger is the morning DJ followed by Dave Otto in the afternoon. Jeff Butler DJs on the weekends.

KUOM – Radio K

Frequency: 770 AM

Genre: University of Minnesota College Radio – Alternative music

KUOM is the University of Minnesota’s student-run, non-commercial station. Genres include independent, ambient, metal, hip-hop, jazz, punk, reggae and more. The station aims to promote local musicians.

WCCO – WCCO News Radio

Frequency: 830 AM

Genre: News

WCCO provides local and national news as well as weather updates. Dave Lee hosts the weekday morning news, and Mike Max hosts the weeknight sports show.

KTIS – FAITH 900

Frequency: 900 AM

Genre: Northwestern College Christian radio

Started in 1949, the goal of KTIS is to nurture Christian spiritual growth. Programs on this nonprofit station feature Christ-centered preaching, teaching and conversations.

KTNF – The Progressive Voice of Minnesota

Frequency: 950 AM

Genre: Liberal talk radio

KTNF is a liberal talk station offering news and local and national programming. Shows include Democracy Now!, The Thom Hartmann Show, The Stephanie Miller Show and The Union Edge.

KKMS – AM 980 The Mission

Frequency: 980 AM

Genre: Christian talk radio

Program topics cover Bible studies, family issues and more. Hosts include Eric Metaxas, Alistair Begg, Dr. J. Vernon McGee and Jay Sekulow.

WCTS – The Bible Station

Frequency: 1030 AM

Genre: Baptist Christian radio

WCTS began in 1965 as a ministry of Central Seminary. Programming features Bible teachings and conservative Christian music.

KYMN – The One

Frequency: 1080 AM

Genre: News, talk and adult alternative music

This station features community voices, news, weather, sports and a wide-range of musical programming. Jeff Johnson hosts the morning show followed by The Wayne Eddy Affair.

KLBB – KLBB The Music of Your Life

Frequency: 1220 AM

Genre: Oldies, nostalgia

Since 1949, KLBB has been playing timeless favorites from artists such as Frank Sinatra, Ella Fitzgerald and Barbara Streisand. You’ll also hear current artists such as Michael Buble’ and Diana Krall. The station is also the home of the St. Paul Saints, the Green Bay Packers, Stan Turner’s All Request Lunch Hour and the Super Saver Show.

​WWTC – The Patriot

Frequency: 1280 AM

Genre: Conservative talk radio

One of the oldest radio stations in the Twin Cities, WWTC’s Programming includes national shows hosted by Michael Medved, Mike Gallagher, Dennis Prager and more. Local news is also featured.

WLOL – Relevant Radio

Frequency: 1330 AM

Genre: Catholic talk radio

WLOL offers programs for Catholic listeners that cover topics such as family, relationships, politics, social concerns and news. You’ll hear programs including Father Simon Says, Go Ask Your Father, The Inner Life and The Drew Mariani Show.

KMNQ – Radio La Invasora

Frequency: 1400 AM / 1470 AM

Genre: Contemporary Spanish radio

The station airs regional Mexican music. Most programs are broadcast in Spanish.

KYCR

Frequency: 1440 AM

Genre: Business talk

KYCR airs news and talk shows covering finance and business.

Radio shows feature Bloomberg’s Ken Prewitt and Tom Keene, Dave Ramsey and Mark Pearson.

KDWA

Frequency: 1460 AM

Genre: Community, news and talk radio

KDWA features content for listeners in Hastings and Prescott counties. Programming includes news, sports, weather and talk shows.

KSTP – 1500 ESPN Twin Cities

Frequency: 1500 AM

Genre: Sports

This Minnesota sports station covers the Vikings, Timberwolves, Wild, Twins and Gophers. Weekday programs feature Mike & Mike in the Morning, Garage Logic, SportsTalk and The Ride with Reusse.
